@declan_barpixel So the nuance is that there's two. One is thermal management bottlenecks (liquid cooling, copper life extension, etc).

$AEHR sits in the manufacturing side for semi yield. Heat is used to stress test to see potential defective units for early failure.

Since chips run at extreme temperatures, a defect causing early life failure is high. So they need to test every chip at extreme heat.

